'''Umarbek Eshmurodov''' (born 30 November 1992) is an Uzbekistani [[association football|footballer]] who currently plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Uzbekistan Super League]] club [[FC Nasaf|Nasaf]] and [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|umar-eshmuradov/297303}}</ref><ref>[https://globalsportsarchive.com/people/soccer/umar-eshmurodov/119914/ Player profile in globalsportsarchive.com]</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Instagram |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/DEFeXZFtYtO/?igsh=MWVxb3Rrb3kybW15bg== |access-date=2024-12-27 |website=www.instagram.com}}</ref>

Eshmurodov made his debut for the [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan senior national team]] on 23 February 2020 in a [[friendly (sport)|friendly]] match against [[Belarus national football team|Belarus]].<ref>[https://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/25444/Uzbekistan_Belarus.html Uzbekistan 0–1 Belarus]</ref>

Named to the Uzbekistan national team squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://t.me/uzpfl/77948|title=UzPFL|website=Telegram|access-date=2026-05-29}}</ref>

